## Utility & Helper Files

### Utility Files
- **Pattern**: `*.ts` for utilities
- **Location**: [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils)
- **Examples**:
  - [src/utils/api.ts](mdc:src/utils/api.ts) - HTTP client
  - [src/utils/logger.ts](mdc:src/utils/logger.ts) - Logging utilities
  - [src/utils/env.ts](mdc:src/utils/env.ts) - Environment validation

### Hook Files
- **Pattern**: `*.hook.ts` for custom hooks
- **Naming**: Start with `use` prefix
- **Example**: `useLocalStorage.hook.ts`, `useBlogPosts.hook.ts`

## Database & Model Files

### Model Files
- **Pattern**: `*.ts` for database models
- **Location**: [src/models/](mdc:src/models)
- **Naming**: PascalCase matching entity name
- **Example**: [src/models/BlogPost.ts](mdc:src/models/BlogPost.ts)

### Model Naming Convention
```typescript
// Model class naming
export class BlogPost extends Model<IBlogPost> {
  // Implementation
}

// Interface naming (prefix with I)
interface IBlogPost {
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  content: string;
}

// Type naming (no prefix)
type BlogPostStatus = 'draft' | 'published';
```

## Test Files

### Test File Organization
- **Pattern**: `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts`
- **Location**: Adjacent to source files or in `__tests__` directories
- **Examples**:
  - `src/services/blog.service.test.ts`
  - `src/services/__tests__/blog.service.test.ts`

## Barrel Exports

### Index Files for Clean Imports
Create `index.ts` files for clean imports:

```typescript
// src/services/index.ts
export { BlogService } from './blog.service';
export { AdminService } from './admin.service';
export { GenerationService } from './generation.service';
export { EstimatorService } from './estimator.service';

// src/managers/index.ts
export { BlogManager } from './blog.manager';
export { ValidationManager } from './validation.manager';
export { AIManager } from './ai.manager';
export { EstimatorManager } from './estimator.manager';
```

## Class & Method Naming

### Class Naming
- **Services**: `[Domain]Service` (e.g., `BlogService`)
- **Managers**: `[Domain]Manager` (e.g., `BlogManager`)
- **Components**: `[ComponentName]` (e.g., `Header`, `ProjectSlider`)

### Method Naming
Follow verb-first, noun-second pattern:

```typescript
// CRUD operations
createPost(), getPost(), updatePost(), deletePost()

// Query operations
searchPosts(), fetchData(), countItems()

// State operations
initService(), startProcess(), stopProcess()

// Batch operations
batchCreate(), bulkUpdate(), multiDelete()
```

